<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1916-11-13T15:36:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1916-11-13T15:36:00-05:00" n="946" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d946">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/19854</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Consul <persName type="from">Canada</persName> to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Consulate</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Vera Cruz</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-11-13T14:00:00-06:36">
                                    <hi rend="italic">November 13, 1916, 2 p.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Down train on the Inter-Oceanic wrecked between Perone and Jalapa on the
                            11th, cause not yet known. Vera Cruz papers admit 150 killed. Some
                            Americans reported killed or injured. Exceedingly difficult to verify.
                            Will report names when known.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Canada</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>